    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hardware, typically used in the interior of a building, that is usually functional and treated as part of the decorative scheme, such as doorknobs and window latches.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010771/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Materiaal dat men doorgaans binnen in een gebouw gebruikt en gewoonlijk een praktische en decoratieve functie heeft, zoals deurklinken en raamknoppen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一般用於建築物內部的五金，通常做為整體裝飾的一部份但又兼具功能性，如球形門把與窗閂。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
